<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Thank you for downloading Bika LIMS. Please see the <a class="internal-link" href="installation-verification">Installation Verification</a> page</strong></p>
<table class="invisible two_column_table">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>
<h3>Note to Testers</h3>
<p>With this release, please concentrate (and try to break) the LIMS' setup and basic workflow for Samples, Analyses, Analysis Requests and Worksheets. Please do test Analysis profiles, Specifications and Worksheet templates</p>
<h2 class="Subheading">Feedback</h2>
<p>Don't hesitate to post questions, comments and suggestions to the Bika mailing lists: Bika <a class="external-link" href="https://groups.google.com/forum/?hl=en#%21forum/bika-design">LIMS design</a>, <a class="external-link" href="http://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/bika-users">Users</a> or <a class="external-link" href="http://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/bika-developers">Developers</a>. Please log issues in the <a class="external-link" href="http://sourceforge.net/tracker/?func=browse&amp;group_id=145464&amp;atid=762012">public Bika bug tracker</a> at SourceForge.net. <strong>NB</strong> - assign issues to 'lemoene'</p>
</td>
<td>
<h2 class="Subheading">Set-up data request<br /></h2>
<p>We standardised open XLSX<strong> </strong>spreadsheets that can be used   to configure the LIMS with setup data of the user's choice. Please contribute setup information to guide us    in pre-populating each of the Bika branches,  e.g. Water, Health, Interlab, etc.</p>
<h3><a class="internal-link" href="setup-data-in-this-installation">Test data</a></h3>
<p>For the purpose of testing, we populated this   instance with data of uniform   nature for most setup items, e.g. Analysis specifications,   QC, uncertainties, turn-around time, precision, price   etc. Please see <a class="internal-link" href="setup-data-in-this-installation">Setup data used to configure this installation</a></p>
</td>
</tr>
